CARACAS , April 20 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- The World Bank is ready to give Venezuela the biggest support possible to back its economic recovery , World Bank President James Wolfensohn said in Washington today .
The aid will come after Venezuela reaches an agreement with the International Monetary Fund -LRB- IMF -RRB- , said Wolfensohn .
The World Bank support will be aimed at reforms in the financial sector and payment of social programs .
Wolfensohn will meet in Washington Sunday with Venezuelan Finance Minister Luis Raul Matos Azocar , who is in the U.S. capital to brief the bank on the economic measures announced Monday by the Venezuelan government .
He is also trying to speed up the negotiations with the IMF .
The Venezuelan minister said that in addition to an agreement with the IMF , he also expects to sign an accord with the World Bank and the Inter - American Development Bank before returning to Caracas next week .
Venezuelan financial sources estimate that the loans of each of these institutions could be up to 1.5 billion U.S. dollars .
